<br>
The voice had returned to haunt her, the same maddening voice that drove her to throw herself off the high cliff of the Frontier Mountains ever so long ago.  He had returned... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Your Goddess is dead, she has forsaken you Malaehi... the Gods are more mortal than you think...&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi quickly got out of her destroyed bed, donned a robe and fled out of her estate as fast as her horse would take her.  By nightfall, she had entered the city of her Gnome, Katta Castellum.  Barging in, unannounced, Malaehi ran up the stairs and into Xendapus Fabink's sleeping quarters.  <br>
<br>
The noise was deafening as she entered the room.  Malaehi was on her guard searching for the dragon who must be hiding in the Gnome's room.  But, there was no dragon, just a wee wizard, curled up into a ball on a tiny bed, snoring so loudly the walls and floor shook.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Gnome... gnome?&quot; </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->she gently shook Xend's shoulder to wake him up.  He lept up into the air, brandishing a sword in one hand and a dagger in the other, slicing and screaming wildly <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Die! Die! DIE!!!&quot;.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi leaped back in time, saving herself from certain death.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;GNOME!  It's me!!&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xendapus blinked, eyes coming into focus <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Elf?!  Bah, what is this?&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi was still in shock, seeing her wild-eyed Gnome, dual wielding in black silk pajamas and a pink sleeping cap.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;What's this?&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The wizard quickly hid the weapons behind his back, tossing them across the room with a whistle and an innocent grin.  The long tassel from his pink nightcap flipped over his face, tickling his nose.  He blushed and ripped the cap off quickly.<br>
<br>
Malaehi rushed into his arms and hugged him tightly.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;The voice is back, Gnome.  I am so scared!&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  He hugged her in return, kissing her elven ears whispering, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;You are safe with me, Mala.  Come, you need sleep, more talk in the morning.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
With a few muttered words and a pull on a cord, his bed expanded into a King sized one.  Buzzing clockwork robots busied about the room, putting on sheets and adding thick warm blankets and pillows.  Xend crawled up on the bed and pulled Malaehi in, then tucked her under the sheets nicely and kissed her nose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Sleep now, I'll be over here keeping watch, ok elf?&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  He picked up his sword and his knife and sat at the foot of the bed, peering into the darkened room, protecting his wife-to-be.<br>
<br>
Malaehi drifted off to sleep quickly and into a dreamscape.  She found herself walking in a castle filled with crazy sights and sounds, wild laughter and uncontrolled screams.  In front of her was a tall, female wearing a beautiful diaphanous gown of black.  She was skeletally thin with pale skin. Long, black fingernails extended from her bony hands, to match her slinky gown. Her face was smooth - no features marred its sleek surface other than two empty black eye sockets. Long black hair flowed back from two massive brass horns at her temples.<br>
<br>
The enchantress recognized her immediately and tried to run, but Terris Thule just laughed and summoned Mala back to her side.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Twice you have tormented me, slaying my minions, trying to destroy me in the name of your Goddess of Love.  Well, you will see what has become of her and the other so called Gods of Norrath.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Entering a vast ballroom, through a crimson fog she saw the pantheon of Norrathian Gods dancing on the white and black checkerboard floor.  They were tiny and doll-like, moving about like marionette puppets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Behold the glorious Gods!  Do you want to know why your goddess never answers your prayers anymore, enchantress?  Do you?!&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi looked on in horror and Terris Thule held up a limp body of a beautiful Barbarian female, dressed in resplendent white robes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Behold your Goddess, Erollisi Marr!&quot; </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Terris threw the doll like Erollisi to the floor and summoned Cazic Thule over.  As the puppet approached, he grew larger and larger, until he reached his full height, towering over all in the room.  Terris pushed Malaehi into his arms and she tried with all her magic to escape, but she was held fast in Cazic's viselike grip.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Summon your Goddess to save you now, enchantress.&quot; </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Terris Thule laughed maniacally as Cazic Thule opened his huge mouth to swallow Malaehi whole.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;ELF!!  ELF!!&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A stinging slap woke Malaehi up from her dream, and she peered into the gaunt, worried face of her Gnome.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Bah, FINALLY!  Are you ok??  You have slept for a fortnight!  I have summoned every priest and shaman I know to awaken you.  You almost seemed...&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Xendapus cringed, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;.... dead&quot;.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi was weakened and disoriented looking around the room and seeing many faces.  Her mind filled with that mad voice saying:  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;...the deities are more mortal than they think...the deities are more mortal than they think...&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
