<br>
The home of Bristlebane.<br>
<br>
Malaehi ventured to the Temple of Veeshan and waited patiently to join a war party to travel safely through the lair of the fierce Dragons and enter the Plane of Mischief.<br>
<br>
She spent the next week wandering the walls of the Castle until she finally found what she was looking for.  The ballroom matched the scene from Malaehi’s dream perfectly.  It all made perfect sense now.<br>
<br>
She found Erollisi Marr and threw herself down at the feet of the Goddess and wept.  But, the Goddess stared across the room with glass eyes and an empty smile, dancing around, mindlessly.<br>
<br>
The voice whispered in her ear… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Yes, it is true.  You have put your faith in a puppet.  You have fought for no one but yourself and those around you, enchantress.”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi whirled around quickly and at last saw the one who’s voice had haunted her.  He was a human, but wraithlike in appearance, wearing the garments of a prisoner.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Who are you!?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The gaunt man chuckled and leaned upon a staff wearily, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“I am called many things… The Forsaken… the UnGod … the Mad… but, what is a name?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> he shrugged and hobbled through the crimson fog, disappearing.<br>
<br>
Malaehi turned back to her Goddess and gently gathered the doll into her arms and hugged her to her chest.  Murmuring words of forgiveness she stepped into a blue-grey portal and left Bristlebane’s abode.<br>
