<br>
Riding her mount, Kingwell, through Lesser Faydark, she recalled laying eyes on the fearful Cazic Thule when he faced off with the tree-hugging sprite Tunare.  The result was a ruined land.  Later she would see Cazic Thule in his own realm and eventually trod across his fallen body.  He was no more than a mighty, powerful beast; nothing to be deified.<br>
<br>
But, what of the rest?  Terris Thule, Saryrn, the Zek twins and Bertoxxulous, … all so called Gods, but lay dead like cattle.<br>
<br>
Praise be to the Gods of the light…<br>
<br>
Malaehi paused and shifted in her saddle.  Kingwell nickered softly, warning the enchantress of an intruder.  The frail man emerged from the Faydark fog and caressed Kingwell’s soft nose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Where were those Gods of the light when this land was cursed?  Why would they not instantly come to your aid when you called?  Why did they allow so many to suffer and perish in battle….”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> His voice grew louder into a shout, echoing through the forest… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Only to allow you to be resurrected and die again?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
He turned to the forest and raised his staff  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Where are you when we need you?  Why do you toy with us?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
He paused and crouched low to the ground and listened, like a crazed person… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Shh... You hear that?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi listened intently, straining to hear.  <br>
<br>
Suddenly the man was upon Kingwell’s back and behind Malaehi in the saddle, holding her tight with his staff across her throat, choking her.  Kingwell took off into a terrified run through the forest at breakneck speed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Call for Erollisi NOW!!!  Do IT!!  Where is she?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi closed her eyes and focused her magic on escaping in anyway, but the man was relentless with his grip, laughing in her ear the whole time.  She prayed to her Goddess, but remembered that her Goddess was a doll, stuffed away in her backpack tied to Kingwell’s saddle.  She had to do something fast, she could not breathe.  She sent her thoughts out into a pure clear stream of thought. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Help me, my love&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Call to her… CALL to any of them… they ARE DEAD!!!  Or they just do not CARE!  Do you hear me?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Tears and the sharp cold wind stung Mala’s cheeks as she felt Kingwell take flight into the air.  The sharp smell of sulfur struck the air as a thunderbolt bounced harmlessly off the back of the madman.  Below on the ground, stood Xendapus chanting and firing off explosions aimed at the madman.<br>
<br>
Then the world went black and tilted left.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
Malaehi woke up in Xendapus’ room, again with his worried face near hers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“There, there she is!  Bah, elf!  You will be the death of me!” </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The gnome sighed.  Mala struggled to speak, but the Gnome put a finger over her lips saying:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“I found something you may want to snuggle with!” </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> He cackled and hopped off the bed and returned with the Erollisi Marr puppet in his hands.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Look!  A Dolly!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> he rambled on missing the look of shock and terror in the enchantress’ eyes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“… just tuck her under your chin and snuggle up for a while.  I need to run out and let everyone know you are fine… hush hush just sleep!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi waited for Xend to leave, before crawling out of bed, grabbing her things and gating back to Plane of Tranquility.  She entered her home on the hill and walked around to her meditation garden.  She settled in and slipped into a trance and deep thought.<br>
<br>
Hours later, she got up refreshed and determined.  She summoned Kingwell and put the doll into his saddleback and sent him off to graze.  Her courier came in with a message.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Milady, evil has invade the land of Tunare and the Council of Faydark and the ancients of Erollisi Marr seek your aid in stopping them.”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi spat in disgust, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“after the abuse the Ancients of Erollisi put me through … torturing me because I fell in love… because I gave myself to a male.  NOW, they want my help…”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi recalled the searing pain of being flogged and starved for her “crime”, for breaking her vow of chastity; they would have taken her life, had it not been for the intervention of Kae, the mysterious enchantress who was a member of the Council.<br>
<br>
She had left the sect of the Goddess and continued to worship her on her own.  But, to what avail…<br>
 <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
