<br>
Her call was returned with familiar voices… Krastus, the evil Knight who has hunted by her side for ages, aye hating her to the core, but protecting her more often than not.  Then the chillingly evil voice of the dead himself, Patron of the House Rea’Morda, beckoning the enchantress in a mocking manner, to join in on the hunt.  <br>
<br>
As she rode Kingwell through the battle scarred land, she recalled the times where the evil one himself had summoned her corpse from the dead, aiding her in battle many times.<br>
<br>
One by one familiar voices, Cortusa, Kogbender, Maedaria, Charaniki, and more.  Voices whom she was told she should hate because of the God they follow.  But, she never hated them.  No, the love of the Goddess impelled Malaehi to convince these lost souls to stop their evil ways and return to the light from where they were snatched ever so long ago by their evil Gods.  Now, she was ordered to slay these for invading Tunare’s realm?!  <br>
<br>
She rode closer to the war party.<br>
<br>
The coldest voice cut through the land, the one whom she feared the most:  Rusalka, Matron of the House, High Priestess of Innoruuk.  The same one who brought Malaehi back from the dead countless times, who stood side by side as they brought Innoruuk to his knees.<br>
<br>
She paused in thought as she rounded the bend and looked down at the hunters. She frowned and decided to disobey the orders of the Faydark Champions, ripping the missive to shreds.  She would not attempt to slaughter these people, nor die trying.<br>
<br>
Approaching the party she expected to be killed as swiftly as they killed the pumas.  But, she was greeted and invited to join in.  Mala tried again to dissuade them from hunting in these holy lands… but even those words sounded dead on her tongue.<br>
<br>
What made these lands holy and Innoruuk’s defiled?<br>
<br>
The voice of laughter resounded in her ears, the voice of the madman, the voice of the Forsaken.  He was Zebuxoruk. And he was right.<br>
<br>
Malaehi joined in the battle and fought furiously, just as she had done in the other realms of the Gods.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
The next day, she was with another army in the Halls of Honor, where she stood on top of the corpse of Mithaniel Marr, twin of her Goddess and a worthy foe.<br>
<br>
Malaehi threw her head back and roared in victory!<br>
<br>
Faith in the Gods was dead to her; however, faith in those she hunted with took its place in her heart.  She was scared, no doubt, but free. <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
